text: Could you please tell me where I'm going from here? That depends where you want to go, the Cat said. I don't care too much where... she started explaining to Alicia. In that case, it doesn't matter where you go. The Cat interrupted. Whenever she gets somewhere, Alicia ends up explaining. Oh, my God! You'll always get somewhere, the Cat said, if you walk enough. Alice in Wonderland, 1865
title: Lógica II
author: Lewis Carroll
